### Code Conventions
- Functional components only (`const ComponentName: React.FC = () => {}`).
- Chakra UI's `sx` or props-based styling preferred over external stylesheets.
- Framer Motion animation props inside Chakra components when needed.
- Structure 3D scenes declaratively via `@react-three/fiber`.
- Always validate prop types via TypeScript interfaces.
- Avoid unnecessary libraries. Use built-in APIs or Chakra utilities where possible.
- Use hooks properly (`useEffect`, `useMemo`, `useCallback`) with correct dependencies.

Always review the full component and its UX — prioritize elegance, functionality, and alignment with Visen AI’s black & green visual identity.
